    lead_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    lead_source TEXT,
    lead_status TEXT,
    date_created TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE marketing_campaigns (
    campaign_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE,
    budget DECIMAL
);</t><stat>select lead_name, lead_source from leads where date_created between '2022-01-01' and '2022-06-30';</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE leads (

CREATE TABLE Audiences (audience_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY, audience_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, description TEXT);</t><stat>SELECT * FROM Campaigns JOIN CampaignMetrics ON Campaigns.campaign_id = CampaignMetrics.campaign_id;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE CampaignAudiences (campaign_id INT REFERENCES Campaigns(campaign_id), audience_id INT REFERENCES Audiences(audience_id), PRIMARY KEY (campaign_id, audience_id));

    customer_name TEXT,
    email TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE products (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name TEXT,
    price DECIMAL
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_id INT,
    ad_content TEXT
);

    customer_name TEXT,
    email TEXT
);

    customer_name TEXT,
    email TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE products (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name TEXT,
    price DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE interactions (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id INT,
    ad_id INT,
    interaction_type TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE ads (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_id INT,
    ad_content TEXT
);</t><stat>SELECT * FROM products WHERE price BETWEEN 50 AND 200;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE campaigns (

    product_name TEXT,
    price DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE campaigns (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_name TEXT,
    start_date DATE,
    end_date DATE
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_id INT,
    ad_content TEXT

    customer_id INT,
    ad_id INT,
    interaction_type TEXT
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_id INT,
    ad_content TEXT
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_name TEXT,
    email TEXT
);

    customer_name TEXT,
    email TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE products (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name TEXT,
    price DECIMAL
);

    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    campaign_id INT,
    ad_content TEXT
);</t><stat>SELECT customer_id, COUNT(*) AS interactions_count FROM interactions GROUP BY customer_id HAVING COUNT(*) > 5;</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE campaigns (
